text: James Minter (13 September 1917 - 2 July 1985) was an Australian cricketer. He played one first-class match for New South Wales in 1938/39. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1917 births Category:1985 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers
